hopobject.body: Please call back later jersey shore prescription drugs Microsoft’s plan was not meant to be a technological advancement, but rather to move money to developers (and to Microsoft) and away from the used game industry. While they did have some nice, but poorly-executed ideas for ways gamers can use this system, I don’t think the solution to the used games industry is to obliterate it. There’s a place for its advantages. I think the best way to solve this problem is some kind of partnership between the developers and the stores.
